{{!
    @template mod_jitsi/view_recording_video

    A recording row with an embeddable video player (GCS or raw Dropbox) plus the
    AI generate dropdown, watched-segments bar, attendance heatmap and AI content
    accordion. The complex AI/segments/heatmap blocks are pre-rendered in PHP and
    injected as raw HTML.

    Context variables required for this template:
    * inplacename string - pre-rendered inplace-editable recording name
    * timecreated string - localised creation date
    * candelete bool, canhidetoggle bool, visible bool, canedit bool, recordid int, cmid int
        - see mod_jitsi/view_recording_actions
    * aidropdown string - pre-rendered AI generate dropdown (may be empty)
    * videoid string - DOM id for the video element
    * sourcerecordid int - jitsi_source_record id
    * embedurl string - playable video URL
    * barhtml string - pre-rendered watched-segments bar (may be empty)
    * heatmaphtml string - pre-rendered attendance heatmap (may be empty)
    * aiaccordion string - pre-rendered AI content accordion (may be empty)

    Example context (json):
    {
        "inplacename": "<span>My recording</span>",
        "timecreated": "1 January 2026",
        "candelete": true,
        "canhidetoggle": false,
        "visible": true,
        "canedit": true,
        "recordid": 5,
        "cmid": 12,
        "aidropdown": "",
        "videoid": "jitsi-video-9",
        "sourcerecordid": 9,
        "embedurl": "https://storage.googleapis.com/bucket/rec.mp4",
        "barhtml": "",
        "heatmaphtml": "",
        "aiaccordion": ""
    }
}}
<h5>{{{inplacename}}}</h5>
<h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">{{timecreated}}</h6>
<div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-end gap-1 mb-1">
    {{> mod_jitsi/view_recording_actions }}{{{aidropdown}}}
</div>
<video id="{{videoid}}" controls style="width:100%;max-width:100%"
    data-sourcerecordid="{{sourcerecordid}}" data-cmid="{{cmid}}">
    <source src="{{embedurl}}" type="video/mp4">
</video>
{{{barhtml}}}
{{{heatmaphtml}}}
{{{aiaccordion}}}
<br>
